''Cowboy Bebop'' has been released in three separate editions in North America.

The first release was sold in 2000 individually, and featured uncut versions of the original 26 episodes. In 2001, these DVDs were collected in the special edition ''Perfect Sessions'' which included the first 6 DVDs, the first ''Cowboy Bebop'' soundtrack, and a collector's box. At the time of release, the art box from the Perfect Sessions was made available for purchase on The Right Stuff International as a solo item for collectors who already owned the series.<ref>{{cite web |title=Cowboy Bebop box set "box" available separately |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2001-11-07/cowboy-bebop-box-set-box-available-seperately |publisher= [[Anime News Network]] |date=2001-11-07 |accessdate= 2009-04-28}}</ref>

The second release, ''The Best Sessions'', was sold in 2002 and featured what Bandai considered to be the best 6 episodes of the series remastered in [[Dolby Digital]] 5.1 and [[DTS (sound system)|DTS]] surround sound.<ref>{{cite web |title= Otakon 2002: Bandai Panel |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2002-07-29/otakon-2002-bandai-panel |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=2002-07-29 |accessdate=2009-04-28}}</ref>

The third release, ''Cowboy Bebop Remix'', was also distributed on 6 discs and included the original 26 uncut episodes, with sound remastered in Dolby Digital 5.1 and video remastered under the supervision of Shinichiro Watanabe. This release also included various extras that were not present in the original release.<ref>{{cite web |title= New Cowboy Bebop Special Edition |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2005-02-16/new-cowboy-bebop-special-edition |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=2005-02-16 |accessdate= 2009-04-28}}</ref> Cowboy Bebop Remix was itself collected as the Cowboy Bebop Remix DVD Collection in 2008.

A fourth release in [[Blu-Ray]] format was released on December 21, 2012 exclusively in Japan.<ref>{{cite web |title= Cowboy Bebop BD Box to Include Novel, Ein Picture Drama |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-08-03/cowboy-bebop-bd-box-to-include-novel-ein-picture-drama |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=2012-08-03 |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref><ref name="Cowboy Bebop Official Website">{{cite web |url=http://www.cowboy-bebop.net/ |publisher=Sunrise |title=カウボーイビバップ |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref>

In December 2012, newly founded distributor Anime Limited announced via Facebook and Twitter that they had acquired the home video license for the United Kingdom. Part 1 of the Blu-Ray collection was released on July 29, 2013, while Part 2 was released on October 14. The standard DVD Complete Collection was originally meant to be released on September 23, 2013 with Part 2 of the Blu-Ray release but due to mastering and manufacturing errors, the Complete Collection was delayed until November 27.{{citation needed|date=December 2013}} Following the closure of Bandai Entertainment in 2012, [[Funimation]] and [[Sunrise (company)|Sunrise]] had announced that they rescued ''Cowboy Bebop'', along with a handful of other former Bandai Entertainment properties, for home video and digital release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Funimation Adds Cowboy Bebop, Escaflowne, Outlaw Star and More|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-08-10/funimation-adds-cowboy-bebop-escaflowne-outlaw-star-more|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=10 August 2013}}</ref> Funimation released the series on Blu-ray and DVD on December 16, 2014.<ref name="narelease">{{cite web|title=Release Date for Cowboy Bebop|url=http://www.funimation.com/blog/2014/08/09/release-date-for-cowboy-bebop/|publisher=Funimation|accessdate=31 August 2014}}</ref><ref name="ANN 2014-12-16">{{Cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-12-16/north-american-anime-manga-releases-december-14-20/.82255|title=North American Anime, Manga Releases, December 14–20|work=Anime News Network|date=16 December 2014|accessdate=2015-12-06}}</ref> The series was released in four separate editions: standard DVD, standard Blu-ray, an Amazon.com exclusive Blu-ray/DVD combo, and a Funimation.com exclusive Blu-ray/DVD combo.<ref name="narelease"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Cowboy Bebop Blu-ray Slated for N. America in December|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-08-09/cowboy-bebop-blu-ray-slated-for-n-america-in-december/.77378|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=10 August 2014}}</ref>

